description: MetaMorph is an open-source framework that leverages the power of Large Language Models (LLMs) to process, extract, and transform messy, unstructured, or heterogeneous columns of metadata into structured, machine-readable formats to enhance machine learning pipelines and predictive models across any domain.

This repository showcases a collection of Python projects and tools developed for machine learning validation, automation frameworks, and automotive ADAS systems. The portfolio highlights AI fine-tuning, data validation, test automation, and business application development.

This repository offers a fully automated, object-oriented machine learning framework that providing a scalable framework for efficient model training, evaluation, and logging. This 100-day plan is designed to build expertise toward becoming an AI Engineer in the space industry, balancing machine learning (ML), physics, astronomy, and space applications. It draws from key skills like Python/ML programming, data analysis, physics simulations, and AI frameworks (e.g., from web searches on essential AI/space skills).

The framework involves the usage of diverse molecular representations, powerful ensemble learning techniques, and interpretable model development strategies.

This project focuses on predicting the severity of Social Anxiety Disorder (SAD) using a multi-modal machine learning framework. The dataset integrates demographic, lifestyle, psychological, and physiological features. Several models were developed and compared, including Random Forest, XGBoost, Support Vector Classifier (SVC).

This project develops a machine learning framework for credit card fraud detection, addressing severe class imbalance and overlap.
